     <td id="main_content"> <h1>Emergency Management</h1> <p>During incidents of national significance, the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) provides support to certain National Response Framework emergency support functions. <a href="http://www.fema.gov/emergency/nrf/">The National Reponse Framework</a> sets forth guidelines for all response partners to prepare for, and provide a unified response in the event of any domestic incident.</p> <p>The USGS serves the Nation by providing reliable scientific information to describe and understand the Earth; minimize loss of life and property from natural disasters; and manage water, biological, energy and mineral resources. The USGS has a special scientific focus for FY 07 and beyond on lessening the adverse impacts of natural hazards - - volcanoes, earthquake, hurricanes, landslides, wild fires, and floods.</p> <p>See also <a href="http://pubs.er.usgs.gov/publication/fs20123061">United States Geological Survey (USGS) Natural Hazards Response Factsheet</a></p> 
      <div style="float: left; width: 48%;"> 
